    "Consequently, dynamic operations on multi-dimensional learned indexes necessitate efficient updates to both the underlying data layouts (e.g., grids or partitions) and the learned models (e.g., PGM-Index).",
    "Among the few learned indexes that are capable of handling dynamic operations, their efficiency in terms of insertion, deletion, and dynamic query processing typically falls short when compared to conventional indexes, such as R-tree and kd-tree variants.",
    "Performance on extended geometries (Q8)The previously presented experimental results and discussions focus on point geometries, which are generally adopted by most existing multi-dimensional learned indexes.",
    "In this section, we evaluate the query processing efficiency when extended to box geometries.",
    "We synthesize bounding box datasets by augmenting three datasets, Uniform, FourSquare, and OSM, where the details can be found in Sect. 4.2."
